docs.text: cult films are never mainstream .

docs.text: the casual viewer of a cult film will look at it and be repulsed and confused , yelling out 'what the hell is that ? ' .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: fans of these sorts of movies will be laughing at every other second at all the 'hidden jokes' they missed the first time around while normal movie watchers will look at them like they're insane .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the rocky horror picture show , recently re-released in a 'special edition' to video , is the mother of all cult films .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: like some other cult films , most notably little shop of horrors , the rocky horror picture show is a musical with a twisted edge to it .

docs.text: this movie begins out innocently enough- a couple get engaged at a friend's wedding and get a flat tire in the middle of the night while it's raining .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: they go to a castle to try to use the phone .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: little do they know that the castle is owned by dr . frank n . furter , a mad transexual transvestite scientist who has recently created a creature he will use for personal reasons .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the acting is pretty good overall .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: tim curry ( home alone 2 , legend ) is over-the-top as frank n . furter .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's interesting to see that this movie was one of future oscar winner susan sarandon's ( dead man walking ) first film- she plays janet , the girlfriend of brad majors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: even the singer meatloaf is in it ! !

docs.text: the songs are all very good yet twisted in their own way .

docs.text: all the actors sing their songs with no dubbing from other actors- kind of a bad thing .

docs.text: barry bostwick ( brad majors ) tries to sing as does susan sarandon , but tim curry is clearly the most professional having extensive stage experience .
